<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Name on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/name/</link><description>Recent content in Name on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/name/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin Unresolved Reference — Name Not Found Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/unresolved-reference/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/unresolved-reference/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="unresolved-reference--name-not-found-fix"&gt;Unresolved Reference — Name Not Found Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An unresolved reference error occurs at compile time when Kotlin cannot find the referenced variable, function, class, or property. This is one of the most common compile errors in Kotlin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kotlin must be able to resolve every name you use to a declared symbol. If the name doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, isn&amp;rsquo;t imported, or isn&amp;rsquo;t visible, the compiler reports an unresolved reference error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ENOTUNIQ (errno 55) — Name Not Unique on Network Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-55/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-55/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-enotuniq-errno-55--name-not-unique-on-network"&gt;Linux ENOTUNIQ (errno 55) — Name Not Unique on Network&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOTUNIQ (errno 55) means the name is not unique on the network. This error occurs when a program tries to register a network name (such as a hostname or service name) that is already in use by another machine on the network. It is distinct from EADDRINUSE (errno 98) because ENOTUNIQ specifically refers to name uniqueness, not address port binding.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ImportError — Cannot Import Name</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/import-version/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/import-version/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="importerror--cannot-import-name"&gt;ImportError — Cannot Import Name&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;ImportError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;cannot import name &amp;lsquo;X&amp;rsquo; from &amp;lsquo;Y&amp;rsquo;&amp;rdquo; is raised when you try to import a specific name from a module, but that name doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist in the module. This can be due to typos, version differences, or incorrect import paths.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When using &lt;code&gt;from module import name&lt;/code&gt;, Python looks for the specified name in the module&amp;rsquo;s namespace. If the name doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, &lt;code&gt;ImportError&lt;/code&gt; is raised. This is different from &lt;code&gt;ModuleNotFoundError&lt;/code&gt;, which means the module itself cannot be found.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>** (NameError) undefined function</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/name-error3/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/name-error3/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;NameError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you try to call a function that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist in the current scope. This can happen when the function is not defined, not imported, or you&amp;rsquo;ve made a typo in the function name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in function name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function not imported with &lt;code&gt;import&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;alias&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Module not compiled or loaded&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling private function from outside its module&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Typo in function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;puttln(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (NameError) undefined function IO.puttln/1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use correct function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;puts(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Not importing the function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;defmodule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Foo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; bar, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;:ok&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bar()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (NameError) undefined function bar/0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Import or alias the module&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;defmodule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyModule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Foo&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;only&lt;/span&gt;: [&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; test, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;: bar() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# works&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Undefined function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;nonexistent(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (NameError) undefined function String.nonexistent/1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Module not loaded&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;reverse([&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# works if Enum loaded&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyCustomModule&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;func()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (NameError) undefined function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Private function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;defmodule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Secret&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;defp&lt;/span&gt; hidden, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;:private&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Secret&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;hidden()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (NameError) undefined function Secret.hidden/0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/argument-error4"&gt;ArgumentError: wrong number of arguments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/function-clause"&gt;FunctionClauseError: no function clause matching&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>